<chapter
	id="management">

	<title>Managing &THIS.PLATFORM; JAIN SLEE with &MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM;</title>

	<section id="main_view">
		<title>&MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM; <acronym>JAIN SLEE</acronym> Plugin Main View</title>
		<para>This section gives an overview of the main page of &MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM; <acronym>JAIN SLEE</acronym> Plugin.</para>
		
		<para>In order to access the page, go to the top menu and select <menuchoice><guimenu>Resources</guimenu><guisubmenu>Servers</guisubmenu></menuchoice>. A list will be presented, where <acronym>JAIN SLEE</acronym> server is listed. Click on it to access server details.</para>
		
		<para>You should have something similar to the following snapshot.</para>

		<figure>
			<title>&MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM; <acronym>JAIN SLEE</acronym> Plugin Main View.</title>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata width="300px" align="center" fileref="images/img-jopr_slee_main_view.png" format="PNG"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<para>&MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM; <acronym>JAIN SLEE</acronym> Plugin Main View</para>
				</textobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</figure>

		<para>As you can see in the left side menu you have the  components that can be managed by &MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM;:</para>

		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem>
				<para>Deployable Units</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Resource Adaptors</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para><acronym>SBB</acronym>s</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Services</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>

		<para>Each one will be described and explained in a separate section.</para>

		<para>Event Router and its Executors are not part of the components of JAIN SLEE but, they are crucial part of its internal workings.</para>

	</section>
	
